FBIS4-36464 "drnes111_c_94006" FBIS-NES-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 Egypt Al-Baz: Country `Closely Watching' Yemen Crisis Al-Baz: Country `Closely Watching' Yemen Crisis NC0806165794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 8 Jun 94 NC0806165794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Dr. Usamah al-Baz, first Foreign Ministry under secretary and director of the President's Office for Political Affairs, has stated that Egypt is closely watching the situation in fraternal Yemen out of its concern for the Yemeni people's interests and the Arab nation's interests in this strategic part of the Arab homeland. He said that Egypt hopes fighting among the sons of fraternal Yemen will stop as soon as possible. It also hopes that the Arab League and UN efforts on this regard will succeed. Al-Baz made this statement after receiving Lakhdar Ibrahimi, envoy of UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali, who later departed for Sanaa.
